               <head>Biography of Abu Bakr, First Caliph, autograph copy</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tārīkh al-khilāfat al-ūlá by Mawlavī ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50036870 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85112612 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000556" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16781-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A historical account of the caliphate of <persName key="person_37713877" role="subject">Abū Bakr al-Ṣiddīq, the first caliph</persName> of the Muslims (d. 13/634), on whom see e.g. <persName key="person_108266459" role="oth">W. Montgomery Watt</persName>, ‘Abū Bakr’, EI2, I, pp. 109-111. This work was composed by the Afghan scholar <persName key="person_f7272" role="aut">Mawlavī ‘Abd al-Ḥaqq</persName> and completed in 1352/1312/1923, as is shown by the title page (f. 1r) and colophon.
                        </p>
                        <p>This is the autograph manuscript of a text which appears never to have been published. Included at the end (f. 117r-v) is a table of contents. The author cites among his sources Ibn Khaldūn (Kitāb al-'Ibar), Ibn Khamīs (unidentified: not, presumably, the famous Tilimsanī poet), Tārīkh al-khulafā’ (by al-Suyuṭī), Kitāb al-Imāma va l-Siyāsa (formerly misattributed to Ibn Qutayba), Vāqidī (al-Waqidī’s al-Maghāzī), and ‘Aṭā’ Ḥasan Bayg (not identified).</p>
                        <p>Begins: Basmala  Ḥamd-i bīḥadd va sanā’-i bī‘add Ma‘būd-i ins va jānn va Khāliq-i har dū jahān, Zāt-i kāmil al-ṣifātī-rā sazāst ki ba-manṭūqa-’i ‘Mā khalqt al-jinn va l-ins illā li-ya‘budūn’ Jinn va ins-rā barā-yi  ‘ibādat va ma‘rifat-i khwīshtan az katm-i  ‘adam...</p>
                        <p>Ends: Ḥaẓrat-i ‘Umar rẓ namāz-i janāza-’i ū-rā khwānd va ‘Umar va ‘Usmān va Ṭalha va ‘Abd al-Raḥmān pisarash ū-rā dar qabr nihādand va sar-i ū nazd-i shāna-’i Rasūl Allāh ṣ nihāda shud va qabr-i ū-rā laḥd karda būdand  Raẓiya Allāh ta‘ālà ‘anh va ‘anhum ajma‘īn </p>
                        <p>Colophon, f. 116r. Completed on Wednesday 18 Asad 1312, or 17 Rabī‘ al-sānī 1352/9 August 1933, by the author. </p>
                        <p>Clear, though amateurish, cursive quasi-naskhī in blue ink. 19 lines. Off-white laid paper. 117 folios, paginated as 234 pages. 211 x 168 mm.; text lines ca. 170 x 124 mm.  Red half leather with worn boards covered with patterned black paper.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from Mr. N. Madjnun, 8 January 2010.</p>
